The course is meant for those language users, who have acquired the language level of A2.2, but who feel that the use of language structures need some explanation and mastering. It is recommended that the student has completed the first part of the grammar course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of this course is to develop a learner's skills to use various every day language structures,  mainly in written texts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student - recognises grammar structures in written text in English and is able to find an adequate expression in Estonian; - can use modals, conditional sentences, adjectives in various contexts, adverbs, reported speech and simple passive voice;  - knows the structure of sentences and can use the correct word order in different speeches; - uses acquired knowledge in oral as well as in written communication.
